WAKEFIELD SERVICE STATION, Inc., Plaintiff-Appellee, v. The TEXAS COMPANY, Defendant-Appellant. No. 216. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 1, 1937. Albert E. Van Dusen, of New York City (Herman Block, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. M. Walter Solomon, of New York City, for appellee.

Before SWAN and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
